# DDoS Attack Sequence Diagram

This document illustrates the sequence of events in a **Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attack** targeting a company's web server, using Mermaid syntax.

## ðŸ“Š Sequence Diagram

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Attacker
    participant BotNet
    participant Firewall
    participant WebServer
    participant MonitoringSystem

    Attacker->>BotNet: Send command to initiate DDoS attack
    loop Massive request traffic
        BotNet->>WebServer: Send high-volume HTTP requests
    end

    WebServer->>Firewall: Forward incoming traffic for inspection
    Firewall->>MonitoringSystem: Log and analyze traffic volume
    MonitoringSystem-->>Firewall: Detect anomaly, suggest IP blocking

    Firewall->>BotNet: Block traffic from known bot IPs
    WebServer-->>LegitimateUsers: Deny service or respond slowly
